PROGRAM:

import java.util.Scanner;
public class Seasonchecker {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);     
        System.out.print("Enter the month (1-12): ");
        int month = sc.nextInt();
        if (month >= 3 && month <= 5) {
            System.out.println ("Spring Season");
        } else if (month >= 6 && month <= 8) {
            System.out.print("Summer Season");
        } else if (month >= 9 && month <= 11) {
            System.out.print("Autumn Season");
        } else if (month >= 12 && month <= 1) {
            System.out.print("Winter Season");
        } else {
            System.out.print("Invalid month! Please enter a value between 1 and 12.");
        }           
        sc.close();
    }
}

OUTPUT:
Enter the month (1-12): 5
Spring Season
Enter the month (1-12): 11
Autumn Season
Enter the month (1-12): 7
Summer Season
Enter the month (1-12): 1
Winter Season

DESCRIPTION:
This is a simple program to find the season of a month by entering the number of the month it will check the month and then prints the appropriate output for the program.
